author: @fanel1900toamna
text: I'm running  this demo on a GeForce GTX 770 OC (Compute capability 3.0, 1536 CUDA cores) with 4GB of video memory. The tensorflow model (ssd_mobilenet_v1_coco_2018_01_28) takes as much video memory as it possibly can (3.5GB) and the framerate is a joke :) . I get a somewhat constant 0.15 FPS (GTA runs at 800x600). Oddly enough, even without running GTA I still get the same FPS.  @Harrison maybe you should do a demo using YOLO (https://pjreddie.com/darknet/yolo/). I think it is much faster than these models and there's plenty of python binding libraries for it. (https://github.com/madhawav/YOLO3-4-Py , https://github.com/gliese581gg/YOLO_tensorflow)
